# Deployment Constraints

## Forbidden Commands

Never run: `pm2 restart`, `systemctl restart`, `nginx -s reload`, `kill -9`, or any service restart shortcut.

## Permitted Deploy Workflow

Deploy only via `/www/study_tool`:

1. `cd /www/study_tool` and pull if needed
2. Stop: `pm2 stop navo-im` (stop and start are separate steps)
3. Build: `npm run build` (shared → server → web)
4. Start: `pm2 start navo-im`
5. Verify health/logs

## Build Order

`shared` must build before `server` and `web`. Root `npm run build` enforces this.

## Required Env Vars

`JWT_SECRET`, `AI_API_KEY`, `PUBLIC_BASE_URL` — server exits without them. See root `.env.example`.

## Dev Proxy Gotcha

Vite proxies to port 4000 by default; server defaults to 8080. Set `PORT=4000` in `.env` or update `web/vite.config.ts`.
